net.hudup.core

Interface PluginManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Firer

    public interface PluginManager
    Plug-in manager is responsible for discovering and managing registered recommendation algorithms. The class that implements PluginManager is Firer. Alg is the most abstract interface for all algorithms. Every algorithm has a unique name. Every algorithm is registered in system register table and identified by its name. Such system register table is modeled as RegisterTable class. Actually, plug-in manager discovers automatically all algorithms via their names at the booting time and requires PluginStorage to add such algorithms into register tables represented by RegisterTable classes. After Hudup framework started, it is easy to retrieve any any algorithms by looking up algorithms in register tables from PluginStorage. Please pay attention that system register tables are stored in a so-called plug-in storage which is represented by PluginStorage class.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

    • Method Detail

      • fire

        void fire()
        This is the first method which needs to be called firstly for any Hudup application. This method is called one time at boot time for any Hudup application. In current implementation, there are two important tasks of fire method as follows:
        1. Create default directories such as working directory and directory of knowledge base.
        2. Call method discover() to discover and register all algorithms (from class path and libaray of Hudup framework) into PluginStorage.

      • isFired

        boolean isFired()
        Testing whether fire() method was fired.
        Returns:
        whether fire() method was fired.

      • discover

        void discover()
        This method discovers automatically all algorithms via their names, which initializes and updates plug-in storage PluginStorage. Packages are specified in Hudup property file. If these packages are not specified, all packages are browsed.

      • discover

        <T> java.util.List<T> discover(java.lang.Class<T> referredClass)
        Getting a list of instances belonging referred class. Packages are specified in Hudup property file. This method does not affect plug-in storage.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of returned instances.
        Parameters:
        referredClass - referred class. If this referred class is null, all classes are retrieved.
        Returns:
        list of instances belonging referred class.

      • discover

        <T> java.util.List<T> discover(xURI storeUri,
                               java.lang.Class<T> referredClass)
        Getting a list of instances from store and referred class. Packages specified in Hudup property file are not used because this method uses store URI. This method does not affect plug-in storage.
        Type Parameters:
        T - object type.
        Parameters:
        storeUri - store URI. If this store URI is null, current directory is used.
        referredClass - referred class. If this referred class is null, all classes are retrieved.
        Returns:
        list of algorithms from store and referred class.
